this video is killing me. outside of Kobe being our LA King, he was a daddy. after losing my father, mother-in-law and having a miscarriage recently and suddenly, death is an odd thing for me. my heart has grown watching everyone mourn in solidarity, which is the soul reason i am a sports fan, it‚Äôs one of the few things that brings us together. i have been and will always pray for the families involved in this tragedy, but i ask that, in general, our hearts ache for those that don‚Äôt have the media coverage to share their spark. may we all work hard to inspire those around us, or the world, as Kobe did. that every child gets their chance to be a true legend. to harness their talents, strive for excellence and bring our teams to victory. but for those who don‚Äôt have that opportunity, i pray your small acts are never forgotten, and your family is forever wrapped in the love of your community. and most importantly- let‚Äôs not underestimate each other‚Äôs dreams. the world is ours! also very time you make a basket - may KOBE!
